==English==
===Noun===
'''bishop''' (''plural'' '''bishops''')

#A high ranking official in the Catholic church who governs a [[diocese]], or a similar official in other denominations and religions.
#{{cattag|Chess}} A piece that may be moved only diagonally.

===Etymology===
From Old English ''[[bisceop]]'' < Latin ''[[episcopus]]'' ([[overseer]], [[supervisor]]) < Greek [[επίσκοπος]] (epískopos) < prefix [[ἐπι-]] (''epi-'', over) + [[σκοπός]] (''skopos'', sight).

